<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-621-574  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 621 574.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Sept 11 1989 v35 n1775 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Panel urges HDTV initiative. (National Advisory Committee onSemiconductors, high-definition television)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robertson, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An interim report to President George Bush from the NationalAdvisory Committee on Semiconductors recommends government supportfor the US high-definition television (HDTV) industry.andP;  A jointindustry-government initiative to develop HDTV would secure the USelectronic industry's competitive position on the world market,according to the report.andP;  The collapse of the consumer electronicsindustry in the US has also contributed to the decline of Americansemiconductor manufacturers.andP;  So far the White House has not takena position on HDTV and government officials are divided on theissue.andP;  President Bush has asked Congress to exclude HDTV fundingfor the Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency program for FY1990.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     High definition televisionForeign CompetitionGovernmentProduct Development.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>